[{"id":"VH978590","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"16 measures of music for violin in treble clef. The key signature has one sharp and the time signature is two-four. The first sequence occurs in measures 4 and 5. The notes are eighth note F5, sixteenth E5, sixteenth D5, eighth E5, sixteenth D5, sixteenth C-sharp5, eighth D5, sixteenth C-sharp5, sixteenth B4, eighth C-sharp5, sixteenth B4, and sixteenth A-sharp4. The second sequence occurs in measures 9 through 11. The notes are eighth note D5, quarter G5, eighth F-sharp5, eighth B4, quarter E5, eighth D5, eighth G4, quarter C5, eighth B4.\" height=\"223\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH978590.g01.png\" width=\"800\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following statements best describes the <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">two</span> melodic sequence patterns in the excerpt above?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH978590_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The first sequence descends by thirds, and the second sequence descends stepwise.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The first sequence descends stepwise, and the second sequence descends by thirds.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Both sequences descend stepwise.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Both sequences descend by thirds.</p>"],"answer":1}]